title: Woman, teens arrested in Sydney drug raids
text:
Share on Twitter 
A GROUP of eight syndicate members have been arrested in police raids this morning following a police investigation into drug supply in Sydney’s southwest. 
Seven simultaneous raids were conducted in Fairfield, Cabramatta West, Smithfield and Elizabeth Hills at 6am this morning after police investigating gang activity uncovered links to supply of cannabis in the area. 
Eight people in total have been arrested, including a woman, four men and three teenage boys. 
The investigation was lead by detectives from the State Crime Command’s Middle Eastern Organised Crime Squad (MEOCS) and Fairfield Local Area Command established Strike Force Barcom which was established in March 2016 to investigate violent acts and associated criminal activity in the Fairfield area. Police raid a Cabramatta home this morning. Picture: Channel Seven Source: Channel 7 
The investigation was assisted by strike force investigators, the assistance of South West Metropolitan Region Enforcement Squad and the Public Order and Riot Squad. 
The suspects have been taken to local police stations, where they are expected to be charged with drug supply and criminal group offences. 
Investigations are continuing and further arrests are expected. 
The arrests come after a series of gang-related shootings in the Fairfield area last year, including the shooting of Assyrian gang member Antonio Hermiz, 20, in broad daylight last month.
